publicationXrefd36.standardName: Cancer-associated fibroblasts regulate endothelial adhesion protein LPP to promote ovarian cancer chemoresistance.

pathway.author: [Khanspers, Fehrhart, Egonw, Eweitz]

comments.content:
Proposed signaling pathways by which MFAP5 induces LPP expression and increases the permeability and motility of endothelial cells via cytoskeleton rearrangement.
The activation of the MFAP5-mediated signaling cascade in endothelial cells up-regulates LPP expression and subsequently promotes the motility of endothelial cells and the permeability of the endothelial cell monolayer. 

Adapted from supplemental figure 11 from [https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/articles/PMC5785271/ Leung et al].
